caption: I can't tell you how much times I have zip pass this place, so my coworkers told me I should venture inside.  Ergo, my breakfast experience.  Best coffee, is busy with deliveries but I went inside to see how things are done.  The place is streamline for take-out only, the stools seat were remove and seating area was taped off.  Everyone expect for one person was wearing a mask. Everyone, has a task and the person who handles money does touch the food unless it packaged.  A tidbit for coffee drinkers. Best used a table spoon rather then a teaspoon.  Just something to think about when asked how many sugars.  The food is delicious and fresh. You must try it.

This place is small and due to covid can only accommodate a maximum of 12 guests for done in. The food is good and reasonably  priced. Seems to be a very popular  spot for locals to grab a quick bite.
Everything was fresh, delicious and well packaged, prices are reasonable. I ordered breakfast, pancakes, bacon and eggs w/grits, everything was how it should be and cooked correctly. Love this place.

Best breakfast spot in the neighborhood. I have been ordering for years and never had an issue with my food. Yeah, sometimes food may take longer, but that’s because it’s a busy spot. Donuts and pastry goods are freshly baked. Can’t go wrong with the breakfast platters.
